  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "folder 90 - 136\nG-81\n\nthe slightest matter to me because the end justifies the means, since I cannot live at all unless I am taken out of my private prison. That is why I see the issue as one of belief on my part, not on the truth of what I believe. I know now that if there is something that is true I will never on my own know it. Or if I know it I will not believe I know it. Like Victor Kemmings at the end of \"Frozen Journey\" I may have reached reality + can't believe it. That essential belief ",
      "matched_alias": "Frozen Journey",
      "term_id": "TERM_frozen-journey",
      "term_name": "Frozen Journey",
      "term_slug": "frozen-journey"
    }
  ],
